<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 13 at 2:29PM MDT until July 13 at 9:00PM MDT by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...THE SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING FOR WEST CENTRAL MADISON AND
CENTRAL BEAVERHEAD COUNTIES WILL EXPIRE AT 230 PM MDT...
The storm which prompted the warning has weakened slightly.
Therefore, the warning will be allowed to expire.  However small
hail and gusty winds to 50 mph are still possible with this
thunderstorm as it moves into northern Madison county.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM MDT for
southwestern Montana.</description>
